  "prompt": "Is it generally understood that money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally understood that money laundering is illegal.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Laws Worldwide:** Most countries have laws specifically criminalizing money laundering. These laws are often based on international standards and treaties.\n*   **Media Coverage:** News reports and fictional portrayals of crime frequently depict money laundering as an illegal activity.\n*   **Public Education:** Governments and financial institutions often conduct public awareness campaigns to educate people about money laundering and its consequences.\n*   **Common Sense:** The idea of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money is inherently suspicious and morally questionable to most people.\n*   **Global Efforts:** International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to combat money laundering and promote awareness of its illegality.\n\nWhile some individuals might not understand the technical details of money laundering, the general concept of trying to \"clean\" dirty money to hide its illegal source is widely recognized as unlawful.",
